{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2652"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of watches and clocks"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2652"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :watch-clock/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :materials-safety :precision-quality-integrity]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :watch-clock-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "WatchOpsAdvisor ⊣ Watch & Clock Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for watch and clock manufacturing (movement-
 assembly/casing/regulation/testing lines producing finished mechanical/
 quartz watches and clocks) -- not direct movement-assembly/testing-
 equipment control authority and not chronometer/accuracy-certification
 authority (e.g. COSC/ISO 3159 compliance mark). Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct movement-
 assembly/testing-equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate
 block, permanent chronometer/accuracy-certification-authority block
 (this actor never self-issues a COSC/ISO 3159 compliance mark),
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged production quantity, double-schedule
 guard, product-type validation, accuracy-test-result plausibility
 validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern
 flagging (materials-safety/battery-cell-hazard/precision-defect)
 ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch`
 is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
